parameters.text:
=Analyze the security alert data provided below. Pay close attention to the `title`, `severity`, `status`, and especially the `comments` to understand the final outcome.

Alert Data:
ID: {{ $json.id }}
Azure Tenant ID: {{ $json.azureTenantId }}
Risk Score: {{ $json.riskScore }}
Severity: {{ $json.severity }}
Category: {{ $json.category }}
Title: {{ $json.title }}
Status: {{ $json.status }}
Description: {{ $json.description }}
Comments: {{ $json.comments }}
Created Date: {{ $json.createdDateTime }}
Event Date: {{ $json.eventDateTime }}
Last Modified: {{ $json.lastModifiedDateTime }}
Vendor: {{ $json.vendorInformation.vendor }}
Provider: {{ $json.vendorInformation.provider }}
Recommended Actions: {{ $json.recommendedActions }}
Tags: {{ $json.tags }}
Sender: {{ $json.sender }}
Recipients: {{ $json.recipient }}

{{
/* Build the userStates block for this alert */
($json.userStates || [])
  .map((u, i) => [
    `User State ${i + 1}:`,
    `  AAD User ID: ${u.aadUserId}`,
    `  User Principal Name: ${u.userPrincipalName}`,
    `  Email Role: ${u.emailRole}`,
    `  Logon Date Time: ${u.logonDateTime}`,
    `  Logon IP: ${u.logonIp}`,
    `  Logon Location: ${u.logonLocation}`,
    `  Risk Score: ${u.riskScore}`,
    `  User Account Type: ${u.userAccountType}`,
    `  On-Prem SID: ${u.onPremisesSecurityIdentifier}`
  ].join('\n'))
  .join('\n\n') || 'No userStates found.'
}}



Respond **only** with valid JSON in exactly this structure:
```json
{
  "analysis_summary": "",
  "final_status": "",
  "recommended_action": ""
}
